Here are paste-ready photorealistic prompts you can use in Nano Banana (or similar image models). Pick one scene or mix details from two prompts.

Information Technology
Prompt:
Photorealistic enterprise data hall or network operations center, cold-aisle containment and cable trays overhead, LED rack indicators in soft bloom, engineer in business-casual and ID badge lanyard at a standing console with multiple panels showing charts and topology (content blurred and unreadable), subtle raised-floor detail and conditioned-air haze, balanced mix of blue server light and warm task lamps, environmental wide shot with believable depth, no readable hostnames, no vendor logos, no faces toward camera.

Shot on full-frame DSLR, 85mm or 35mm, f/5.6–f/8 for clarity, Adobe neutral profile, minimal oversharpening, natural chromatic aberration, real-world imperfections, documentary editorial style.


Science & Technology
Prompt:
Photorealistic applied research laboratory, stainless benches and a fume hood with sash half-open, optical breadboard with mounts and fiber patch cords (labels illegible), researcher in lab coat and safety glasses adjusting an instrument under a flexible arm light, glassware and small tools in organized clutter, neutral-white overhead panels plus practical highlights on metal, faint condensation on a chilled stage window, documentary R&D mood—not stock “eureka” staging—no journal covers, no readable equations on whiteboards, no corporate branding.

Shot on full-frame DSLR, 85mm or 35mm, f/5.6–f/8 for clarity, Adobe neutral profile, minimal oversharpening, natural chromatic aberration, real-world imperfections, documentary editorial style.
